Each week, I try and plan at least one breakfast with a friend to catch up on life & just enjoy each other 💕 might sound silly, but it’s actually a literal “to-do” on my weekly checklist for myself bc I’ve found that (for me personally at least), if I’m not intentional about planning and reaching out, it doesn’t happen!
.
I can so easily get caught up in the day-to-day hustle and with all the urgent and distracting things vying for my attention that I forget to make time for friendships (especially one on one time!). But a few months ago I started making a list at the beginning of the month of friendships I wanted to cultivate. Even the simple act of writing their names down each month has helped me to be intentional about prioritizing time together. I also use that list as a prayer list to remember to be praying for them throughout the month. Personally, I keep it simple and try to limit to only 3 or 4 people so I don’t overwhelm myself.
.
I’m curious, do you have a list of things you do at the beginning of the month? If so, what’s ONE THING you try and do each month??
.
PS:: Dallas friends, have you tried out the new @gatherkitchen location in Preston center?? 💕🙌🏼

This weekend was such a dream 💕 we all came to DC to surprise our sweet friend Rebecca for a bachelorette weekend! My cup is so full 🙌🏼 we love you Rebecca!! 😘
.
Sometimes I get so caught up in the hustle and bustle of life, that I forget how much I NEED some good quality friend time! We were built for community and need each other! But it’s so easy to get caught up in our routines, staying in, cancelling plans or watching Netflix and miss out on the joy and blessing of community and friendship. When I was in high school and college, community and friendships were pretty easy. Everyone was always around and we were together all the time. But gosh, post grad life is different. 🤦🏼‍♀️ it takes a lot more effort and intentionality. I want to encourage you this week to invest in your people! Call that old friend, go to coffee, reach out!

How do you actively pursue community and friendships?

Can I be honest about something? I kinda hate how everyone hypes this up as the most wonderful time of the year. Shoot, I’ve honestly probably even done it on this blog!

And the thing is – it is a great time of year – but it doesn’t mean every day feels like it. I’ve had my fair share of funks during the holidays, and I think it’s one of the hardest times to go through one. It’s like we’re not supposed to feel anything but cheery and totally awesome from November-December.

But that’s not realistic. People have funks all the time, no matter the month, and a lot of the time it’s out of our control. Today on the blog, I’m sharing 4 things to try when you’re in a funk during the Holidays 🎄❤️

Lately, I’ve been pursuing freedom. I want more of it in my life, and specifically in my work and personal journey of spiritual growth. In scripture it says that where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is freedom (2 Corinthians 2:17). We find freedom, life, and peace THROUGH the Holy Spirit.

But, what does that mean?

This verse helps me discern whether I am walking in the Spirit or in my flesh on a regular basis. When I am walking in condemnation or fear, I ask myself, "Is there freedom or life in this?" Nope. In that moment (which is often), I have to consciously pivot AWAY from me and TOWARDS Him. Some days I don't feel the freedom to love others around me well. I feel guarded or I compare. There is no life or peace there because I am loving them with my own strength. Some days I don’t feel freedom to work (and serve) without expectation or need of affirmation. There is no life or peace there either because I am looking to work to satisfy in a way it never can.

In those moments, when I realize I’m trying to do it all on my own, I find freedom in remembering this:: His Spirit can and will equip me. I don't have the power it takes to do it on my own and that’s okay. The Spirit is our Helper. I can ask for help. And so can you 💕 That is SO freeing. And something I need to be reminded to step into every single day!

I hope you found this to be encouraging! I love talking about my faith on stories, but I really struggle to put my experiences into words (and especially into a photo). I’m pushing through that. I’m trying. 💕 I hope you can find some freedom for yourself today I’m asking the Spirit for help, in surrendering whatever it is your struggling with to Him.

Sometimes I talk to myself. Okay, maybe more than sometimes. Typically, I say things like “you’re doing great” or “you can do hard things” or “okay, one step at a time.” And it helps me. Do you do this?

Whether you’re working today or chasing kiddos around, I want to remind you that you CAN do hard things. You might mess up and have to try again, but you can still keep moving - one foot in front of the other. Like I talked about in my stories yesterday, you have what you need to be faithful TODAY.

If you feel stuck or paralyzed by your to-do list (or messy house) this morning, keep reading.

HOW to get UNSTUCK:: start ridiculously small. If you’re feeling overwhelmed with how difficult a task is, then break it down into stupid tiny pieces. It will be easier to take the next step. Do one little thing - the next step. this will build your confidence and get you some momentum. Then do the next.

What’s one thing you’re going to do today? One step?

I just got back to Dallas from a fun little weekend in Austin. And even though it was a short (and fun!) trip, something about traveling (no matter how far or long) always calls for a little post-travel recovery/maintenance before jumping right back into the normal routines of life!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I wanted to share 3 self-care tips for getting back into the swing of things after traveling (or in general)::
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. Drink a lot of water : 🤦🏼‍♀️ I’m so bad at it y’all. BUT it’s so important - especially post-travel. It helps flush out your body and rehydrate you from a day of travel.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2. Write it all down : AKA do a BRAIN DUMP! I love to pull up a seat in front of my fireplace or the couch, put on some chill music, and journal so I can remember my travel experiences while they are fresh on my mind - things I thought about, realized, etc. This also helps me get everything out of my head so I can clear out my head and my heart for the week ahead!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3. Take a hot bath : my favorite part of Sunday nights 🙌🏼 baths help my crazy mind SLOW down! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
How do you wind down after a weekend?

I’m learning that freedom comes from empowering others. Lately, I’ve been feeling so enslaved by social media and just work in general. But shifting my perspective from “I have to do it all myself and do it well” to “let me just serve someone today to the best of my ability” has given me such relief and is slowly taking the self-inflicted weight off my shoulders.

In today's technological culture, everything is connected. We can share ideas and connect with people from all over the world - at any given moment. It's an exciting time really. But within reason - in moderation, with boundaries. This is key.

I've been feeling a little **too** “one with the technology” 😆 …if you know what I mean? And that’s EVEN WITH taking breaks and posting less. I think maybe the breaks haven’t been **as** renewing as I’d hoped bc it was more like pressing PAUSE when what I really need is a REFRESH.

Does that make sense? Like, yeah, it was nice to step away for a minute. But I came back with the same worries, anxieties, and affirmation-seeking spirit. Maybe I could fight it for a few days, but not for long.

Yesterday morning, after meeting with a friend and sharing #allmyFEELS, she told me she was going to pray that I find freedom in my work. I was like, OMG YES. THAT’S WHAT I NEED. Thanks for putting everything into A WORD. That really resonated with me - FREEDOM.

We find freedom when we surrender - when we shift the focus from ourselves to others. When we quit trying to grasp and control and cling so tightly. When we embrace collaboration over competition.

Think about an area of your life where you feel STUCK. Or enslaved. Or just A LOT of pressure? Is it possibly because you’re focusing too much on the outcome? Or trying to do everything yourself? Trying to control every little detail?

What’s one area of your life where you would love to find more freedom?
